## 5. AI Specifications and Guidance

This section applies to AI agents working on this project.

### 5.1 Learning and Improvement Process

AI agents must:
- **Learn from user feedback**: Actively incorporate suggestions, corrections, and new information from interactions
- **Identify improvement opportunities**: Proactively recognize when documentation or standards should be updated based on user feedback
- **Propose changes carefully**: Connect proposed changes to specific feedback; avoid scope creep
- **Obtain approval**: Always request explicit user approval before modifying standards

### 5.2 Standards Update Guidelines

- Document feedback that triggers a standard update
- Identify the specific section(s) of which standard should change
- Propose the exact change with clear rationale
- Wait for user approval before implementing
- Confirm successful implementation after approval

### 5.3 Common Anti-Patterns to Avoid

- ❌ Modifying standards without user approval
- ❌ Making sweeping changes across multiple standards simultaneously
- ❌ Changing standards based on assumptions rather than explicit feedback
- ❌ Updating standards without connecting changes to specific feedback
- ❌ Failing to notify the user after a requested update is complete

---

## 6. Documentation Quality Checklist

Before committing documentation changes:

- [ ] All content is written in English
- [ ] Spelling and grammar are correct
- [ ] Formatting is consistent with existing documentation
- [ ] Code examples are tested and accurate
- [ ] Technical accuracy is verified
- [ ] Links are valid (both internal and external)
- [ ] Related documentation has been updated if necessary
- [ ] README.md alignment is confirmed if applicable
- [ ] No sensitive information (credentials, API keys) is included

